com.team9.finalproject

Class DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team9.finalproject.DataManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DataManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class acts as a database for all of the member, provider, and service data we enter into Chocoholics. It will be initialized once on a machine, and then loaded from a serialized file every other time.
    Author:
    wchampton

      • addService

        public void addService(java.lang.String serviceCode,
                       java.lang.String serviceDate,
                       java.lang.String recivedDate,
                       java.lang.String providerNumber,
                       java.lang.String memberNumber,
                       java.lang.String comment)
        Adds services with the given parameters to serviceList. This is used when you have most but not all of the necessary fields that need to be looked up in order to create a new service.
        Parameters:
        serviceCode: - the service code
        serviceDate: - the date the service happened
        recivedDate: - the date the service was billed
        providerNumber: - the providerID
        memberNumber: - the memberID
        comment: - any comments about the service
